{
  "texts": [
    "See Fig. 8 for an example prompt for the labeling task.",
    "This gives rise to a variety of, previously unencountered, issues such bias, toxicity, and hallucinations.",
    "Some of which make the additional claim that modern models have the capacity to lie (Azaria and Mitchell, 2023) and deceive (Park et al., 2023; Hubinger et al., 2024) (while being careful to not assign beliefs to the AI).",
    "Indeed, both truthfulness and honesty were a part of Grice's original maxim of quality.",
    "Grice's definition of the maxim of relevance (originally presented as the maxim of relation) simply imposes that responses \"be relevant.\""
  ]
}